headline.main: BRITON CALLS ITALY EXAMPLE TO JAPAN; Alexander Warns Tokyo Not to Expect Any Other Fate if She Follows Hitler

lead_paragraph: BLACKPOOL, England, Nov. 29 (U.P.) -- A.V. Alexander, First Lord of the Admiralty, said today that "Japan can expect nothing from Adolf Hitler except what the Italians got."
